    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-03-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-03-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="118" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d118">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Baron <persName type="from">Fava</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Personal.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy
                                        of Italy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-03-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 16,
                                1895</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear</hi> Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Gresham</hi>:</p>
                <p>I am in receipt of your note of this date inclosing a copy of the
                            telegram addressed by you to his excellency the governor of Colorado,
                            relating to the killing of Italians at Walsenburg.</p>
                <p>In reply I hasten to inform you that a copy of said telegram will be
                            forwarded at once to his excellency Baron Blanc, who, I am sure, will
                            share with me the full appreciation of the course taken in this matter
                            by the Federal Government as well as by the governor of Colorado.</p>
                <p>With my personal thanks for your kind communication, I remain, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fava.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
